<TITLE> Three policemen jailed for bribery </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 18 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court Wednesday sentenced three policemen to seven-year rigorous imprisonment in a Tk 15 lakh bribery case. The then Fatullah police chief Ashraful Islam and sub-inspectors Enamul Haque and Miraz Al Mahmud have also been fined Tk 1 lakh. They have to serve one more year in jail for failure to pay the fine. According to case details, the policemen took Tk 15 lakh in bribe for freeing an accused official from a case that centres around the recovery of rotten wheat of Abul Khair Group in Fatullah in Narayanganj. Judge Shamsun Nahar Begum handed down the verdict in the Special Judge's Court-4, set up in the Sangsad Bhaban premises. The court also sentenced Abul Khair Group general manager ASM Mostafizur Rahman and manager Zakir Hossain to one-year rigorous imprisonment for paying the bribe. The two have been fined Tk 10,000 each or have to serve out one more month in jail for failure to pay the amount. The police seized five cargo ships, laden with rotten wheat imported by Abul Khair Group, from Afsar Oil Mill anchorage in Fatullah. Joint forces arrested the three policemen and the two officials of Abul Khair Group on Jan 31 in the act of transferring the bribe. RAB officer Abu Sadeque had filed the case against the five as a plaintiff. The accused testified to court on July 8, pleading innocent to the case and said they were victims of a conspiracy. In court, the two officials of Abul Khair Group alleged torture in custody by the RAB officers. The court framed charges against the five on May 30 and started taking depositions on June 4. bdnew
